name: heat production, mixed logs, at furnace 100kW | heat, central or small-scale, other than natural gas | Cutoff, U
description:
ecoQuery: https://ecoquery.ecoinvent.org/3.10/cutoff/dataset/1940/documentation

This activity represents heat production from combustion of wood logs in Switzerland and is used for the global activity as first approximation (uncertainty factors adjusted accordingly). Wood log LHV=9430 MJ/m3. It is supposed to be representative for average installed technology. The inventory shall be considered valid for wood log boilers with nominal capacities above 50 kW.;;Some emission data are from the late 1990's; key emission parameters (CO, PM, NOx, CH4, NMVOC) have been updated according to latest available data. The activity represents average annual operation including start-stop and part-load operation, which results in a reduced efficiency and increasing emissions compared to manufacturer information.;[This dataset was already contained in the ecoinvent database version 2. It was not individually updated during the transfer to ecoinvent version 3. Life Cycle Impact Assessment results may still have changed, as they are affected by changes in the supply chain, i.e. in other datasets. This dataset was generated following the ecoinvent quality guidelines for version 2. It may have been subject to central changes described in the ecoinvent version 3 change report (http://www.ecoinvent.org/database/ecoinvent-version-3/reports-of-changes/), and the results of the central updates were reviewed extensively. The changes added e.g. consistent water flows and other information throughout the database. The documentation of this dataset can be found in the ecoinvent reports of version 2, which are still available via the ecoinvent website. The change report linked above covers all central changes that were made during the conversion process.]

From delivery of wood logs.

This module describes the combustion of natural wood logs. Included are the infrastructure, the wood requirements, the emissions to air, the electricity needed for operation, and the disposal of the ashes.

processDocumentation.timeDescription: Key emission factors PM, CO, NMVOC, NOx, CH4 were aupdated according to latest available information. Other emission data (which hardly depend on the combustion technology) are from the second half of the 1990Â´s.
processDocumentation.geographyDescription: Inventory represents Swiss conditions and was used as global activity as first approximation.
processDocumentation.technologyDescription: Boiler of average technology installed on market.
processDocumentation.dataTreatmentDescription: This dataset has been copied from an original dataset covering the geography CH. The uncertainty has been adjusted accordingly.

exchanges.description: Reference product scaled to 1. Emission data and amounts of other exchanges in the mathematical relation refer to the input of 1 MJ end energy (in the fuel) and were scaled to the output of 1MJ useful energy (heat). Efficiency provided by the source represents average annual operation including warm-up and cool-down and will therefore be lower than nameplate efficiencies provided by manufacturers,
